cs.OS, cs.AR, cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.SY

This paper discusses the behavior and use of nonvolatile memory DIMMs, which are relevant to operating systems (cs.OS), computer architecture (cs.AR), databases (cs.DB), distributed computing (cs.DC), and system-level software (cs.SY). The paper specifically explores the performance properties and characteristics of Intel's 3D XPoint DIMM, which is relevant to all of these sub-categories.
